{"parse":{"title":"Coherence time (communications systems)","pageid":12205222,"revid":815285716,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Communications_system\" title=\"Communications system\">communications systems</a>, a <a href=\"/wiki/Communication_channel\" title=\"Communication channel\">communication channel</a> may change with time. <b>Coherence time</b> is the time duration over which the channel impulse response is considered to be not varying. Such channel variation is much more significant in <a href=\"/wiki/Wireless\" title=\"Wireless\">wireless</a> communications systems, due to <a href=\"/wiki/Doppler_effect\" title=\"Doppler effect\">Doppler effects</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Simple_model\">Simple model</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Coherence_time_(communications_systems)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Simple model\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In a simple model, a signal <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle x(t)}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle x(t)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d54c275db3a1e620737b58e143b0818107fa5f5c\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:3.979ex; height:2.843ex;\" alt=\"x(t)\"/></span> transmitted at time <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle t_{1}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle t_{1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/cb0768c0bd659f2f84fb5ef9f4b74f336123d915\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:1.894ex; height:2.343ex;\" alt=\"t_{1}\"/></span> will be received as<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (December 2017)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle y_{t_{1}}(t)=x(t-t_{1})*h_{t_{1}}(t),}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>y</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2217;<!-- \u2217 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>h</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle y_{t_{1}}(t)=x(t-t_{1})*h_{t_{1}}(t),}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/3d77306e3eb94e9d41dd4b7955c9fbac54791d3b\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:25.744ex; height:3.009ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle y_{t_{1}}(t)=x(t-t_{1})*h_{t_{1}}(t),}\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>where <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle h_{t_{1}}(t)}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>h</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle h_{t_{1}}(t)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f21d22d86399a1e101ed58e2f89ebd86dad84da1\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:5.645ex; height:3.009ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle h_{t_{1}}(t)}\"/></span> is the channel impulse response (CIR) at time <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle t_{1}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle t_{1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/cb0768c0bd659f2f84fb5ef9f4b74f336123d915\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:1.894ex; height:2.343ex;\" alt=\"t_{1}\"/></span>. A signal transmitted at time <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle t_{2}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle t_{2}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/749fee708b41e7079eabd50d61c8bf3e965db16f\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:1.894ex; height:2.343ex;\" alt=\"t_{2}\"/></span> will be received as \n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle y_{t_{2}}(t)=x(t-t_{2})*h_{t_{2}}(t).}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>y</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2217;<!-- \u2217 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>h</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle y_{t_{2}}(t)=x(t-t_{2})*h_{t_{2}}(t).}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b522dcd397657b27b0e4820d970e14e88c4de337\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:25.744ex; height:3.009ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle y_{t_{2}}(t)=x(t-t_{2})*h_{t_{2}}(t).}\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>Now, if <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle h_{t_{1}}(t)-h_{t_{2}}(t)}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>h</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>h</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle h_{t_{1}}(t)-h_{t_{2}}(t)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/81436249cca62ded7a0ae9038d7730b50fd2f48d\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:14.131ex; height:3.009ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle h_{t_{1}}(t)-h_{t_{2}}(t)}\"/></span> is relatively small, the channel may be considered constant within the interval <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle t_{1}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle t_{1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/cb0768c0bd659f2f84fb5ef9f4b74f336123d915\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:1.894ex; height:2.343ex;\" alt=\"t_{1}\"/></span> to <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle t_{2}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle t_{2}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/749fee708b41e7079eabd50d61c8bf3e965db16f\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:1.894ex; height:2.343ex;\" alt=\"t_{2}\"/></span>.\n</p><p>Coherence time (<span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle T_{c}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>c</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle T_{c}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/66261e3cbed8035b2bf7a9ccb878c786cf7556c6\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.302ex; height:2.509ex;\" alt=\"T_{c}\"/></span>) will therefore be given by\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle T_{c}=t_{2}-t_{1}.}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>c</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle T_{c}=t_{2}-t_{1}.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b828466ca1f2734ff7e33c5f77887c9c4cc5ac62\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:12.675ex; height:2.509ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle T_{c}=t_{2}-t_{1}.}\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Relation_with_Doppler_frequency\">Relation with Doppler frequency</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Coherence_time_(communications_systems)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Relation with Doppler frequency\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Coherence time <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle T_{c}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>c</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle T_{c}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/66261e3cbed8035b2bf7a9ccb878c786cf7556c6\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.302ex; height:2.509ex;\" alt=\"T_{c}\"/></span> is the time domain dual of Doppler spread and is used to characterize the time varying nature of the frequency dispersiveness of the channel in the time domain. The Maximum Doppler spread and coherence time are inversely proportional to one another. That is,\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle T_{c}\\approx {\\frac {1}{f_{m}}}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>c</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x2248;<!-- \u2248 --></mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>f</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi>m</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle T_{c}\\approx {\\frac {1}{f_{m}}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/853c75cc2110c69c621dfdbb65c41874374f4880\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:9.051ex; height:5.676ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle T_{c}\\approx {\\frac {1}{f_{m}}}}\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>where <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle (f_{m})}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>f</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>m</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle (f_{m})}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a31d39b7fa4dd3bfdeddf5560bbe88020f5333b0\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:4.624ex; height:2.843ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle (f_{m})}\"/></span> is the maximum Doppler spread or, maximum Doppler frequency or, maximum <a href=\"/wiki/Doppler_effect\" title=\"Doppler effect\">Doppler shift</a> given by <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle f_{m}={\\frac {v}{c}}f_{c}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>f</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>m</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>v</mi>\n            <mi>c</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>f</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>c</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle f_{m}={\\frac {v}{c}}f_{c}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/757a19807896ccce198a6c85798a111299bc5636\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -1.838ex; width:9.96ex; height:4.676ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle f_{m}={\\frac {v}{c}}f_{c}}\"/></span> with <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle f_{c}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>f</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>c</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle f_{c}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d2b64a46c31800830b9fecc59b22812390e18c05\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.083ex; height:2.509ex;\" alt=\"f_{c}\"/></span> being the center frequency of the emitter.\n</p><p>Coherence time is actually a statistical measure of the time duration over which the channel <a href=\"/wiki/Impulse_response\" title=\"Impulse response\">impulse response</a> is essentially invariant, and quantifies the similarity of the channel response at different times. In other words, coherence time is the time duration over which two received signals have a strong potential for amplitude correlation. If the reciprocal bandwidth of the <a href=\"/wiki/Baseband_signal\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Baseband signal\">baseband signal</a> is greater than the coherence time of the channel, then the channel will change during the transmission of the baseband message, thus causing distortion at the receiver. If the coherence time is defined as the time over which the <a href=\"/wiki/Correlation_function\" title=\"Correlation function\">time correlation</a> function is above 0.5, then the coherence time is approximately,\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle T_{c}\\approx {\\frac {9}{16\\pi f_{m}}}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>c</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x2248;<!-- \u2248 --></mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>9</mn>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>16</mn>\n              <mi>&#x03C0;<!-- \u03c0 --></mi>\n              <msub>\n                <mi>f</mi>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mi>m</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msub>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle T_{c}\\approx {\\frac {9}{16\\pi f_{m}}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/dc576f9a0fd36175b2eb583e5a9cdcdff8a62e5b\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:12.708ex; height:5.676ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle T_{c}\\approx {\\frac {9}{16\\pi f_{m}}}}\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>In practice, the first approximation of coherence time suggests a time duration during which a <a href=\"/wiki/Rayleigh_fading\" title=\"Rayleigh fading\">Rayleigh fading</a> signal may fluctuate wildly, and the second approximation is often too restrictive. A popular rule of thumb for modern <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_communications\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Digital communications\">digital communications</a> is to define the coherence time as the <a href=\"/wiki/Geometric_mean\" title=\"Geometric mean\">geometric mean</a> of the two approximate equations also known as <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Clarke%27s_model&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Clarke&#39;s model (page does not exist)\">Clarke's model</a>; from the maximum Doppler frequency <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle f_{m}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>f</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>m</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle f_{m}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a86985ce29664569bf891b3c2e1350792aa04e7e\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.814ex; height:2.509ex;\" alt=\"f_{m}\"/></span> we can obtain 50% coherence time <sup id=\"cite_ref-shankar2002_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-shankar2002-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-rappaport2002_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-rappaport2002-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle T_{c}={\\sqrt {\\frac {9}{16\\pi f_{m}^{2}}}}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>c</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <msqrt>\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>9</mn>\n              <mrow>\n                <mn>16</mn>\n                <mi>&#x03C0;<!-- \u03c0 --></mi>\n                <msubsup>\n                  <mi>f</mi>\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mi>m</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mn>2</mn>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msubsup>\n              </mrow>\n            </mfrac>\n          </msqrt>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle T_{c}={\\sqrt {\\frac {9}{16\\pi f_{m}^{2}}}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2d169d1a8d0f38f2dad9c417468fb7fe8259cd0c\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -3.505ex; width:15.031ex; height:7.676ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle T_{c}={\\sqrt {\\frac {9}{16\\pi f_{m}^{2}}}}}\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>Usually, we use the following relation<sup id=\"cite_ref-rappaport2002_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-rappaport2002-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle T_{c}={\\sqrt {\\frac {9}{16\\pi }}}{\\frac {1}{f_{m}}}\\simeq {\\frac {0.423}{f_{m}}}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>c</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <msqrt>\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>9</mn>\n              <mrow>\n                <mn>16</mn>\n                <mi>&#x03C0;<!-- \u03c0 --></mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </mfrac>\n          </msqrt>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>f</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi>m</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x2243;<!-- \u2243 --></mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>0.423</mn>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>f</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi>m</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle T_{c}={\\sqrt {\\frac {9}{16\\pi }}}{\\frac {1}{f_{m}}}\\simeq {\\frac {0.423}{f_{m}}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4fca05641d510c6adbba6141801d8a88410feaa8\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:25.099ex; height:6.176ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle T_{c}={\\sqrt {\\frac {9}{16\\pi }}}{\\frac {1}{f_{m}}}\\simeq {\\frac {0.423}{f_{m}}}}\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Coherence_time_(communications_systems)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-shankar2002-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-shankar2002_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">P. Mohana Shankar, <i>Introduction to Wireless Systems</i>, John Wiley &amp; Sons, 2002</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-rappaport2002-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-rappaport2002_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-rappaport2002_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">T.S. Rappaport, <i>Wireless Communications</i>, Prentice Hall, 2002</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2239\nCached time: 20180916195646\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.072 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.210 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 280/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 1890/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 494/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 11/40\nExpensive parser function count: 1/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 1727/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.017/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 830 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   47.706      1 Template:Citation_needed\n100.00%   47.706      1 -total\n 71.18%   33.956  